Not your usual weekend plan!
@cafehawkers in Connaught Place hosted a Tote Bag Painting Workshop  and it was a perfect mix of creativity, food, and calming energy.

From painting unique designs to enjoying delicious mocktails, pasta, and cheesy pizza 
The experience felt more like a creative escape than just another café visit.

Located at L-22, Connaught Place, near Odeon Cinema, Cafe Hawkers blends cozy corners with interactive events that stay with you.

💡Quick tip: You can book your table on @districtupdates for special discounts.

There’s something satisfying about visuals that feel like the product itself.

Here’s a look at our latest product shoot for @shrur_official featuring their Snail Mucin Face Cleanser a product that focuses on hydration, glow, and skin clarity.

We kept the setup minimal, letting the product speak for itself. Soft lighting, natural tones, and crisp detailing helped us bring out the calm, clinical vibe the brand stands for.

Always love working with brands that care about what they’re building.

If your product has a story, we’ll help you show it right.

Rashki Juno, minimal design, classy handbags, everyday bag, structured style, Indian fashion brand, work to weekend, chic carryall, premium vegan leather, style that speaks, timeless elegance, modern minimalism, effortless chic

This fashion show was hosted by Rawls Salon and sponsored by Ohrisons and Diva Jewellery. It was a celebration of tradition, fashion, and festive vibes.

We got the chance to cover the entire event from start to finish. Our Directors was there to capture every important moment.

The shoot began inside the dressing room, where the models were getting ready in traditional outfits and makeup. Every detail was covered from styling to final touch-ups.

Next, We moved to the ramp walk. We made sure to cover each participant equally, focusing on expressions, outfits, and the overall energy of the show.

This shoot was more than just visuals. It was about documenting the effort, teamwork, and vibe of the event in the most natural and clean way.

One place. Three different moods. All in one story.

Thanks & Beyond in Nehru Place is not your usual café.
It has a cozy boho lounge, a peaceful outdoor area that feels like Italy, and a lively bar with some amazing cocktails.

The food is just as exciting  from Turkish grills to sushi and Thai stir-fry, the menu brings together flavours from around the world.

Telling real stories from real places that’s what we do. 🎬

Some cafés are known for their ambience. This one stood out for its experience.

@cafehawkers in Connaught Place hosted a unique paint-on-bag workshop, blending creativity with calm in the heart of Delhi.
Tucked near Odeon Cinema (L-22), the café serves more than just food, it offers a vibe that lingers.

Great food, interactive experiences, and corners full of character, this place deserves a spot on your list.

Pro tip: Book via @districtupdates for some exclusive offers.

Some cafés impress you with their menu.
This one moved me with its mission.

Echoes Café in Paschim Vihar is not a regular place.
The staff here can’t speak or hear  but the way they make you feel is truly special.

We’re proud to bring this story to life through our lens 🎬

If you’re in Delhi, this place should be on your list.
